The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, July 24, 2004 				 Sales spike fails to lift Indo Gulf bottomline
																								July 23 (PTI): Aditya Birla group firm Indo Gulf Fertilisers Ltd has reported a dip in net profit at Rs 7.98 crore in the first quarter ended June 30, 2004 compared with Rs 12.25 crore recorded in the corresponding previous quarter. 																								Net sales, however, rose to Rs 94.67 crore against Rs 40.32 crore registered in the year-ago period, the company said in a release here today. 																								Other income slipped to Rs 6.5 crore from Rs 12 crore last year.																								The company produced 2.38 lakh metric tonne of urea, reflecting a 100 per cent capacity utilisation, the statement said. 																								In the short-term, a deficit in rainfall in certain parts of the country is likely to affect the demand for urea but on a long-term, the fertiliser sector offers an enormous growth potential, the company said. Aptech Q2 net up 61%																								Aptech Ltd has posted a 61 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 5.01 crore in the second quarter ended June 30 against Rs 3.11 crore in the year-ago period.																								Revenue rose by 23.7 per cent at Rs 28.15 crore against Rs 22.76 crore in the April-June period of 2003-04, the company said in a release here today.																								The recent surge in recruitment by the IT services and the BPO industry has re-kindled the interest in IT training amongst students, aiding a growth in students enrolment and revenues, said managing director Pramod Khera.																								Net profit and total revenues for the first-half stood at Rs 7.67 crore (Rs 5.05 crore) and Rs 50.82 crore (Rs 45.41 crore) respectively, it said.Castrol Q2 net rises																								Castrol India Ltd has posted a 15.36 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 47.14 crore in the second quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 40.86 crore in the same period of 2003-04.																								The board has recommended an interim dividend of Rs 4 per share, the company said in a release.																								Net sales rose to Rs 360.73 crore against Rs 308.22 crore in the April-June period of 2003-04, the company said. 																								Net profit and sales for the first half (January-June 2004) stood at Rs 74 crore (Rs 76.6 crore) and Rs 649.1 crore (Rs 556.9 crore) respectively, it said.Aftek Infosys net soars																								Aftek Infosys Ltd has posted a 30.42 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 52.43 crore for the year ended June 30 compared with Rs 40.20 crore recorded in the previous fiscal. 																								Net sales for the 12-month period rose to Rs 138.96 crore against Rs 96.28 crore a year ago, Aftek Infosys said in a release here today. 																								Net profit for the fourth quarter rose to Rs 13.40 crore on a net sales of Rs 36.70 crore, compared with a net profit of Rs 11.31 crore on a net sales of Rs 25.94 crore year-on-year.SKF net doubles																								Bearing manufacturer SKF India Ltds net profit in the second quarter ended June 30 doubled to Rs 12.24 crore against Rs 6.2 crore registered in the same period last year.																								Revenue stood at Rs 144.88 crore compared with Rs 121.8 crore last year, a company statement said.
